    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>How to Give Away $21.8 Billion</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jane Sjogren letter on Jean Strouse's April 16 article on Gates Foundation describes how schlarship winners are chosen</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Last week, I (and some 200 others) spent four days reviewing applications for the Gates Millennium scholarships. This year's funds will go to minority students at all levels of college and graduate studies, not just entering freshmen. The applications are evaluated according to what we know about what makes minority students persist in college and beyond rather than by simply looking at grades and test scores.</p>
        <p>Jane Sjogren  Winchester, Mass.</p>
      </block>
